LessonsLearned:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id="result_box" lang="en"&gt;The causes of the accident are mainly due to weaknesses in risk assessment in relation to:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span id="result_box" lang="en"&gt;• shortcomings in the assessment of risks in terms of consequences;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span id="result_box" lang="en"&gt;• deficiencies in the control of the corrosion phenomenon, in the application of the results of the operational experience and in the revaluation of tanks maintenance frequencies;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span id="result_box" lang="en"&gt;• shortcomings in the adoption of "compensatory" preventive / protection measures in the waves of completion of the works for the realization of double funds.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span id="result_box" lang="en"&gt;&lt;span title="In pratica le misure tecnico/gestionali adottate dal gestore come:
"&gt;In practice, the technical/management safety measures adopted by the operator such as:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="•	i sistemi di protezione passiva dei serbatoi (anodo sacrificale) combinati con il controllo giornaliero dell'integrità dei bacini e dell'eventuale perdita dal trincarino dei serbatoi;
"&gt;• Passive tank protection systems (sacrificial anode) combined with day-to-day control of basin integrity and possible loss from tank trunking;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="•	il controllo del contenuto d'acqua al di sotto della soglia del 0,2 %;
"&gt;• control of water content below the 0.2% threshold;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="•	la movimentazione del fondo dei serbatoi attraverso agitatori per evitare sia la separazione dell'acqua dall'olio sia il conseguente incremento dei processi corrosivi del fondo dovuto all'aggressività dell'acqua;
"&gt;• Moving the bottom of the tanks through agitators to avoid both the separation of water from the oil and the consequent increase in the corrosive processes of the bottom due to the aggressiveness of the water;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="•	l'utilizzo degli inibitori di corrosione;
"&gt;• the use of corrosion inhibitors;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="•	le azioni di intervento immediato contenute nel PEI,

"&gt;• Immediate action in the emergency responce,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="erano ritenute dal gestore sufficienti per garantire l'integrità dei serbatoi nel periodo di manutenzione (10 anni) e tali da far stimare che il rischio di conseguenze in termini ambientali derivanti da questi eventi fosse comunque limitato e che il potenziale impatto potesse interessare una porzione limitata"&gt;were considered sufficient by the operator to ensure the integrity of the tanks during the foreseen maintenance period (10 years) and to estimate that the risk of environmental consequences stemming from these events was still limited and that the potential impact could affect a limited portion &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span title="di superficie, anche nelle peggiori condizioni."&gt;of surface, even in the worst conditions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div id="gt-res-content"&gt;
&lt;div id="gt-res-dir-ctr" class="trans-verified-button-small" dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span id="result_box" lang="en"&gt;However, as early as 2013, after 5 years after the first extraordinary maintenance, there was a loss of containment from 2 tanks. This led the operator to adopt as a definitive protective measure the creation of the double bottom of the first&amp;nbsp; tank and the repair of the trunk of the second one.&lt;br&gt;These events should have led the operator to prevent uncontrolled crude oil releases, to re-evaluate the reliability of its tanks and to adjust maintenance frequencies in relation to its operational experience, that is to say, in view of the the predictions of the state of degradation of tank bottoms.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="trans-verified-button-small" dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span id="result_box" lang="en"&gt;The analysis produced by the operator for the purpose of assessing the consequences of a possible loss of containment and therefore in terms of vertical and horizontal migration speeds of contamination have not been reflected in reality due to the presence of the intubated tract of a buried stream passing accross the plant. Such a channel, the existence of which was not known, constituted a real preferred drainage pathway, with very high hydraulic conductivity in relation to the context, which was necessary for mapping and which would have to be taken into account in calculating the magnitude of the consequences ( horizontal migration speed and extension of contamination).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="trans-verified-button-small" dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;span id="result_box" lang="en"&gt;During the implementation of the mandatory maintenance plan (requested by Authority in 2013) aimed to improve the tank protection equipment (double fund installation), the operator should have promptly implemented&amp;nbsp; at least technical prevention/protection measures of a "compensatory" type, or preventing/monitoring leakage of product from the bottom of the tanks without double bottom and/or mitigate the consequences of such losses (also in the light of the events occurring on other 2 two tank in 2013).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="trans-verified-button-small" dir="ltr"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

EmergencyResponce_Descr:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;On site and off site&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;After being noticed on 3 February 2017 of the presence of Hydrocarbons in the sewage, the operator undertook the following actions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-&amp;nbsp;notifications to the authorities required by the IPPC and Seveso (External Emergency Plan) regulations;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- identification of&amp;nbsp;the route of the piping connected to the sewage well outside the establishment, and&amp;nbsp;of the nature and origin of the contaminant;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- interception downstream of the sewage system by inflatable septum;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- excavation of a trench&amp;nbsp;on the internal side of the establishment in order to intercept any contaminated flow;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- installation of&amp;nbsp;piezometers in order to better define the conceptual model and possible contamination and its distribution;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- analysis of sub soil and water taken during investigations;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- under&amp;nbsp;control of the competent authorities,&amp;nbsp; starting of&amp;nbsp;the remediation of the polluted soil, subsoil and groundwater.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Subsequently the operator provided for the following corrective actions:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- update of the evaluation of risk associated with the tank oil spill;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- double bottom installation on the crude oil storage tanks;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- implementation of an Extraordinary Maintenance Plan;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- update of the tank storage operational control procedure;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-&amp;nbsp;integrity check of buried pipelines;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;- update/issue of concerned&amp;nbsp;HSE IMS procedures taking into account the event occurred:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-periodic inspections on sewage networks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-identification of critical elements/equipment for the environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-safety procedures operational control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-environmental operational control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-management of accidents, injuries, near miss, medical treatments, first aid cases and unsafe acts/conditions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-management of the&amp;nbsp;operational emergency safety measures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-operative control procedure for emergency safety barriers and piezometers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-implementation of surface water monitoring procedure for external areas outside the establishment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;-implementation of the management scheme for the management of oil spills with external impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

AccidentDescription:
&lt;p style="text-align: justify"&gt;The event was verified on February 3, 2017, when a monitoring well located outside the perimeter of the plant was interested by the presence of water contaminated by hydrocarbons that flowed into a sewage pipeline to the consortium treatment plant. &lt;br&gt;The discovery of the hydrocarbons in the monitoring well was possible thanks to the report of technicians of the&amp;nbsp;consortium informing of the presence&amp;nbsp;in the&amp;nbsp; treatment plant of waters seemingly polluted by hydrocarbons. &lt;br&gt;Further investigations (excavations inside the plant area and inspections of sewers outside it) led to the discovery of a widespread groundwater contamination combined with the presence of hydrocarbons at external sewers and consequently the assessing of the existence of an occurring uncontrolled emission of hydrocarbons involving subsoil and aquifer underlying the plant as well as a migration of contamination in areas outside its perimeter.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The results of the surveys carried out on the tanks after their dismantling for the installation of the double hulls made it possible to ascertain that the event consisted in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;nbsp;- loss of containment of one tank caused by corrosion of the bottom,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: justify"&gt;&amp;nbsp;- product leakage in the layers underlying the bottom of the tank itself (foundation side) for the probable presence of cracks in the bituminous (flexible) sheath presumably due to the contact&amp;nbsp;with the annular (rigid) concrete foundation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: justify"&gt;&lt;br&gt;This caused the vertical migration of crude oil from the unsaturated zone to the underlying saturated&amp;nbsp; zone (freatic acquifer) at about 6 meters in depth. &lt;br&gt;Subsequently, the presence below the oil tank of a preferential horizontal way of drainage of groundwater, consisting of the intubated and underground tract of a paleo-ditch, favored the drainage and rapid migration of the hydrocarbon plume into separate phase in the southwest direction and its extension outside the perimeter of the plant.&lt;/p&gt;

Site_Description:
&lt;h5 id="tw-target-text" class="tw-data-text tw-ta tw-text-small" dir="ltr" style="text-align: left; height: 120px"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;The&amp;nbsp; plant is located approximately 2500 m south of a small city centre, in the industrial area.&lt;br&gt;Among the vulnerable territorial / environmental elements within a radius of 2 km (based on the information available in the notification) are the following:&lt;br&gt;N. 3 Inhabited places&lt;br&gt;N. 1 Plant subject to EU Seveso III Directive&lt;br&gt;Other plants not subject to EU Seveso III Directive&lt;br&gt;N. 1 Shallow Acquifer at about 6 meter depth&lt;br&gt;N.2 Rivers located at about 1000 m. down-gradient groundwater flux direction &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5 id="tw-target-text" class="tw-data-text tw-ta tw-text-small" dir="ltr" style="text-align: left; height: 120px"&gt;&lt;span lang="en"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
