Description:
&lt;p&gt;Based on the investigations carried out by the operator, the hazardous substance released is crude oil. The substance is classified as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;P5c - Flammable liquids Category 2 - H225&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hazardous to the acquatic environment in Category Chronic 4 - H413 (Not relevant for Seveso directive)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It has been estimated by the operators a loss of about 400 tons of crude oil.&lt;br&gt;The start of the release has been dated, in particular, less than six months before the date of the event's assessment of &lt;br&gt;3 February 2017. The monitoring carried out on the piezometric network installed for emergency response purpose ruled out the presence of H2S, which is typical of non-stabilized oil. This fact&amp;nbsp;made it clear&amp;nbsp;with reasonable certainty that the oil found in groundwater originated&amp;nbsp;from the storage tanks park located on the north side of the plant&amp;nbsp;where the crude oil flows downstream of a water treatment process consisting of H2S removal. This hypothesis was subsequently confirmed by the results of the inspections carried out on the bottom of reservoirs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
